Well, depends on what you like to write, doesn't it?

What I had in my head was a Fantasy type world where a mountain clan, or small city state, or whatever other government type that fits, is eeking out a living. Maybe not always legally. A tough place that attracts weird people. Our bat is either the leader or an important person in the community, and our male lead is hired to give advice, or improve the local stuff in some way. He's a cut-rate guy, of course. Either a charlatan, a disgraced person, or simply someone who's never been good at his job. Kind of like how a small island nation would be able to hire Cuban doctors, but not English ones.

She's hard-edged and dangerous (and can lift a grown man clear off the ground), he's soft and slippery (and can only barely lift a grown man clear off the ground). Together, they discover... love. Or a momentary lack of hate. Or just the feeling that hugging is really nice when the other person isn't a judgemental asshole. Or they just complement each other in ways no-one would have guessed. Sometimes you really just have to wrap the resident weirdo in your wings for a good feeling. And sometimes you really just have to let the scary bat lady have her way.
